@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
@next "Requirements"
@prev "Copyright"

RainBoot Based Blanker Engine - in short RBBE - is simple commodity for
using virtually any program as a blanker. The idea behind was of course
great RainBoot utility with its' great multimedia (everyone likes this
word nowadays:) features.

Program is @{"freeware" link "Copyright"}.

Click to find out about the @{"requirements" link "Requirements" 0} and the @{"usage" link "Usage" 0} of RBBE.
@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Requirements"
@next "Usage"
@prev "Introduction"
Requirements:

Kickstart 3.0

Libraries: Reqtools.library in the libs: directory
Fonts: Xen.font in fonts: directory

Registered version of RainBoot would be also nice :).

Anything else you want to run as a blanker with RBBE.

@endnode

@node "Usage" "Usage"
@next "Bugs"
@prev "Requirements"

To enable RBBE just copy it to WBStartup directory or run it from
startup sequence.
RBBE is an commodity so you can activate, deactivate or remove it
with Exchange.


Prefs are almost self explanatory :).

RainBoot path        - here you choose where RainBoot is.
RainBoot Script Path - Here you set script name and its' commands
                       eg. c:Misc/Blanker.rainboot MODEID $xxx RTG
Time in seconds      - time to launch script.

Use                  - Use current settings, unfortunately settings
                       will work after old blanker time will pass
                       (this will change in the future)
Save                 - Save current settings
Cancel               - cancel changes
About                - guess what


You can find example RainBoot config in 'BlackMass' drawer.
Run the RBBE preferences and input:
-in RainBoot path - ed. c:Rainboot2
-in RainBoot script path:

-(yourdir)/BlackMass/RBBE_config
                        -for AGA

-(yourdir)/BlackMass/RBBE_config MODEID (your 640x480x8 mode) RTG
                                                         -for CGX

When you'll be testing example config don't get confused with
noises - this is really music, not a bug. 

@endnode

@node "Bugs" "Bugs"
@next "Authors"
@prev "Usage"
Known bugs and limitations.

Most important - if you write RainBoot scripts be sure to remove
%Q command at the end of the script so the script won't quit
itself.

Mouse handling is done in non system way - RBBE is checking state
of keys and mouse and then simulates LMB press for 20 frames.
This could be a problem when pointer reaches top bar - screen could
be mowed or some window on Workbench could be closed or moved for
a while.

When you press 'Use' in RBBE Prefs settings will work after second
start of the blanker. Old blank time should pass first (lame, to
be fixed soon:).

@endnode

